Logic of Marca1: Marca1 is set (i.e., TRUE) when:
Marca2 is FALSE.
Marca1 is already TRUE (keeping it latched) or Out1 is FALSE.
Int1 is TRUE.

Logic of Marca2: Marca2 is set when:
Marca1 is FALSE.
Marca2 is already TRUE (keeping it latched) or Out1 is TRUE.
Int1 is TRUE.

Latch Behavior of Out1: Out1 is set based on Marca1 and Marca2, such that:
When Marca2 is FALSE and either Marca1 is TRUE or Out1 is already TRUE, Out1 remains latched as TRUE.
This setup ensures Out1 holds its state (latched) until specific conditions trigger a reset, controlling Out1’s toggling or retention.

Direct Signal Pass-Through

Boolean Pass-Through: The Boolean inputs Int2, Int3, and Int4 are directly assigned to the corresponding outputs Out2, Out3, and Out4, respectively, allowing these inputs to pass through without modification.

Unsigned Integer Pass-Through: The unsigned integer inputs IntAn1, IntAn2, IntAn3, and IntAn4 are directly passed to outputs OutAn1, OutAn2, OutAn3, and OutAn4, respectively, without any additional conditions.

Conditional Output Logic for Out5 to Out8

Condition for Out5: Out5 is set to TRUE if:
IntAn5 (an unsigned integer input) is greater than 1000.
